// compiler/codegen/nvptx_p7_reduce_sum_test.hexa
// RFC 071 P7 N59 — single-thread sum-reduction source-to-silicon fixture
//
// @version 0.0.1
// @capabilities [pure]
// @phase("parse_only")
//
// This file is a TEST FIXTURE for F-RFC071-E2E-REDUCE-SUM-SINGLE-THREAD-NUMERIC-EQ
// (RFC 071 §4 P7 follow-on to N50 vec_mul `097451f3` + N56 vec_div).
// All prior P3..P6 fires tested ELEMENT-WISE kernels (N input → N output).
// This cycle probes whether the source-to-silicon pipeline (N13 Path B +
// N35 STMT_LOAD/STORE synth + N45 CSE + N28 param-type + N17 to_i64/cmp
// + N29 wider classifier) handles a NON-ELEMENT-WISE shape:
// thread-local FP64 accumulator + back-edge loop + single output write.
//
// Kernel is launched as 1 thread total (1×1 grid, 1×1×1 block) — this
// is the SIMPLEST possible reduction. Multi-thread warp-reduce with
// `shfl.sync` is a separate multi-cycle follow-on. What we test here:
//
//   (a) `var v: f64 = 0.0` lowers to an FP64 Local + initializer
//       STMT_ASSIGN (constant 0.0)
//   (b) the `while idx < n` back-edge becomes a real STMT_BR loop with
//       a header label, body label, and back-edge bra
//   (c) `v = v + a[idx]` lowers to STMT_LOAD (a[idx]) + STMT_BINOP
//       (FP64 add) + STMT_ASSIGN (reuse accumulator slot)
//   (d) `idx = idx + 1` lowers to integer increment on a Local that
//       MUST classify as a NON-fp64 bank (i64 by `n: i64` parameter)
//   (e) `out[0] = v` lowers to STMT_STORE on the kernel-output array
//       with a literal-0 index (i.e. `idx_off = 0 * 8 = 0`)
//
// Kernel name is `reduce_sum` so the falsifier substring-checks
// `.visible .entry reduce_sum` and inspects body for `add.f64` on the
// accumulator + a back-edge bra. We do NOT expect any `// unsupported`
// markers if (a)..(e) all lower; if ANY appear that's a separate
// codegen gap we report honestly.
//
// `@phase("parse_only")` declares this file's role: input to the P7
// emit-driver, not a standalone test runner.

// ── The kernel (gpu/SPEC.md §2 — @gpu_kernel must return void) ───────

@gpu_kernel
fn reduce_sum(a: [f64], out: [f64], n: i64) {
    var v: f64 = 0.0
    var idx: i64 = 0
    while idx < n {
        v = v + a[to_i64(idx)]
        idx = idx + 1
    }
    out[to_i64(0)] = v
}
